Louis S. WEBER, Libelant-Appellee, v. PENNSYLVANIA RAILROAD COMPANY, Respondent-Appellant; Port Reading Railroad Company, Respondent-Appellee. No. 217. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Feb. 10, 1930. Burlingham, Veeder, Fearey, Clark & Hupper, of New York City (Paul Tison and Chauncey I. Clark, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Edmund F. Lamb and Maeklin, Brown, Lenahan & Speer, all of New York City, for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed in open court.
